title: Google voice not calling anyone
content:
I'll say "okay Google, call Nadine," and it will say, "okay, let me get some more information so I can help you with that. Then I'll get a screen that reads, "Get the full assistant experience. With your permission, your assistant can help you with that and more." And below that is a button that says "Get started." 

When I click it, it just takes me back to the original voice command, and I'll say "call Nadine," and it will just keep doing the same thing over and over.

I'd like to ask it to call someone and it just does.
category: Google Assistant and Voice Actions, Google Pixel 3
